What’s van Goghin’ On?: 14962 oozes creativity. Thanks to his mom, who helped develop his love for the arts, this theater major grew up with a strong appreciation for plays, books, and painting. That said, “speechless” is definitely a rare trait for this well-dressed, social guy who is normally quite outgoing and hilarious, constantly telling jokes to liven up the mood. In his alone time, he can be found running, reading a new book, or sitting in the audience at a play.

Engineer with Rhythm: Likable and outgoing, Donor 14966 is a focused student who is driven to become the first engineer in his family.
An accomplished saxophone player, he enjoys playing the blues - but when it comes to dancing he is all about the Latin beats! Although he loves math and can be quite technical and precise in the classroom, he still enjoys the simple things in life like going for a hike or hanging out with friends telling jokes.

When he gets home from work, the problem solving doesn’t stop – he enjoys taking on big projects at home, like installing surround sound, building an attic, or even decorating for Halloween! When he’s not tinkering with something or digging into a book, this 6’2’’ guy takes time to get active by running, playing football, and cycling.

He recalls spending an entire summer with his father converting their garage into a recording studio, where this aspiring composer would write and record his original work. This part-time comedian now holds a degree in Film Scoring, and works full-time for a composer, helping to arrange music for film and television. When he’s not chasing down his music dreams, 15002 likes to write sketch comedy and perform with his improv troupe.

Never one to settle, he even graduated Magna Cum Laude without any debt! As a Public Administration major, he hopes to apply all that he learned in college to help out kids like him. In his free time, this blue-eyed athlete still likes to practice his pole vaulting, which he picked up on his high school track team. Put any obstacle in this ambitious young man’s way, and he’s sure to soar over it!

Patriot and Scholar: This Business Administration major is rightfully proud of his college degree, an accomplishment funded, in part, by his service in the United States military. With his service and college years behind him, this bilingual football star has plenty of options in life, having equal passion for business and Exercise Studies. In his spare time, this athlete participates in dance groups and works out at a martial arts studio.

Handsome Biochemist: Attractive with sweet brown eyes and a kind smile, Donor 15020 has the looks, the brains, and the personality. Friendly, thoughtful, and very considerate, this biochemistry grad student is pursuing a career in research to discover new treatments. His “Express Yourself” highlights what shaped his life, including how he started playing piano, visiting art museums, and going to the symphony when he was just eight years old. In his spare time, he enjoys playing chess, cheering on his favorite soccer team, and learning about different cultures. Passionate about travel and adventure, he once biked to the summit of a volcano in Ecuador!

The Fixer: This Mechanical Engineering major knows a thing or two about cars. Of course, that’s bound to happen when you take one apart and put it back together again! With an athletic build and preppy sense of style, this high school football star always appears put-together. He’ll claim that it’s all an illusion, though, and tell you about the time he fell into an open manhole! Thankfully, no 15022’s were harmed in the making of this bio.

Resilient: 15056 was ready to try out for major college soccer teams… but then he tore his ACL. This positive, resilient guy didn’t let the injury set him back, though. His resourcefulness and passion paid off, and he’s now the starting forward on a college team. Musical Physician: While he’s normally extremely organized, this world traveller once fell asleep on a train through Austria and woke up in Italy! Well Accessorized: This young scholar might have big time ambitions in his law career, but he still knows how to have fun! He believes in hard work and dedication, but also thinks that being empathetic is the secret sauce that has positively impacted his life. Friendly and optimistic, he loves engaging in conversation with anyone from his mail carrier to the baristas at his local coffee shop.

Living the Dream: Donor 15390 is the boy-next-door who followed his childhood dream to eventually grow up and become a firefighter. During high school he pushed his body to the limits, to prepare for his future volunteer career. His leadership abilities and his outgoing demeanor make him the perfect person to train new hires. He is a happy person because he gets to wake up every day and do something that truly makes life worth living.

Artistic Athlete: Donor 15396 enjoys expressing himself through music composition, painting, and photography. He is creative and conveys stories through lyrics, colors, and perspective. You can check out some of his drawings, photos, and lyrics in his Express Yourself. In addition to being artistic, he also earned multiple tennis awards. Kind and thoughtful, he is thankful for his mother’s encouragement and is grateful that he has a career doing what he loves – making art.

Chef Boyardee: Donor 15397 has the uncanny ability to carry on a conversation that is enthusiastic and engaging with just about anyone. He loves to cook, and while he isn’t a professional chef, he has earned the nick-name of chef-boy with his close friends. He does want to take some advanced culinary courses so he can continue pursuing his love of cooking. He has a very mellow demeanor. Growing up near the beach he enjoys all water activities, and being outdoors.

With Honors: Ambitious and eager to learn, Donor 15402 started playing chess when he was just 7 years old. He worked diligently in high school to maintain a high GPA and earned a scholarship to college where he graduated magna cum laude. He continued to achieve his goals by completing a master’s degree in computer engineering and moving to the U.S. This software engineer is grateful to his parents for teaching him the value of education and hard work. When he’s not busy at the computer, he enjoys playing the drums, writing poetry, and hiking.

Cultured & Creative: Passionate about art, Donor 15404 loves drawing and fashion. He has a great sense of style and often wears clothing inspired by Japanese culture. A firm believer in “following your dreams”, he chose a school that specialized in art, and now has a career as a digital editor which utilizes his creative skills. Friendly and positive with an endearing smile, he’s excited to help others achieve their dream of having a family.

Setting the Mood: Donor 15412 enjoys creating art, he likes to paint and will not stop until he feels like the canvas accurately captures the proper mood. He would describe himself as someone with an outgoing personality and tries to seek adventure everywhere he goes. For some people moving to a new country and leaving everyone you know behind would be scary, but not to this donor. He embraced starting over, and meeting new people. He is excited about all the adventures life brings his way, and he can’t wait to see what happens next.

Well Composed: 15423's Express Yourself demonstrates his extensive musical creativity. Music is an integral part of who he is and serves as a creative outlet for the inspiration he finds all around. With an unyielding love of music, and the uncanny ability to work hard, this young professional is well on his way to turning his passion into a career. He loves being connected to the people around him, and with the ability to speak both English and Spanish fluently he has the ability to do so in a larger scale. This donor values family and the life long bond he has with his brother, the older he gets, the closer they become.

Talks the Talk: Thanks to parents that worked for an international resort company, Donor 15434 is quite the experienced world traveler who can speak French and German. Not only did he and his close-knit siblings have the opportunity to travel around Europe, the Caribbean, and the Dominican Republic growing up, he actually spent 7th grade at an international school in Vienna. An outgoing and warm person, he carries a positive attitude no matter where he roams. A serious motorcycle accident he shares in his Personal Essays had a huge impact on his life that he is still learning from today. He has always enjoyed drawing, and uses music and writing poetry to calm his soul.

High Roller: Intelligent and ambitious, Donor 15441 learned addition and subtraction when he was only 3 years old. Gifted in both academics and athletics, this math whiz also earned medals in track. Passionate about bowling, he learned his technique from his grandmother and he’s determined to perfect his score. This busy engineer is taking some time off from his bowling league to spend more quality time with his two kids. With a warm smile and friendly personality, this doting dad cares immensely about his children.

Surfing with Sharks: Donor 15445 is an endlessly curious student of life who loves reading and meeting new people. This outdoorsy donor also enjoys cooking, camping, hiking, and spending time at the beach. He hopes to travel to the Great Barrier Reef to see the vibrant coral. This donor almost always has a smile on his face, especially when he is shredding waves on his surfboard – although he once attracted some unexpected companions out on the waves: sharks!

Food for the Soul: Tall with blue eyes, Donor 15465 is a talented musician and creative cook. This classically trained singer plays the guitar, bass, mandolin, piano, and the violin. Passionate about expression through art, he loves drawing, composing music, and writing songs and poetry. You can read one of his poems in his Express Yourself. Open-minded and easy to talk to, this honor student may have a laidback personality, but he is also sharp and diligent -- graduating summa cum laude from college. When he’s not busy making music, he loves to experiment in the kitchen with new recipes.

Dog Days: Donor 15467 values his family which consists of his wife and two adopted dogs that no one else wanted. He is glad to report that with a little love and compassion their dogs are thriving. Kindhearted and eager to help others, he became a donor so that he could provide the opportunity for others to achieve their dream of having a family. Happy with his job and relationships, he is proud of building a life with the right balance. Getting a full scholarship for his master’s degree, being gifted in art and music, and his knack for building things from scratch are just icing on the cake.

Up for a Challenge: Donor 15472 keeps his analytical mind busy by solving crossword puzzles, playing challenging board games, and participating in fencing. Witty and talented, he has a great sense of humor and a knack for writing. Passionate about movies, he hopes to produce his own film someday. When he’s not working on screenplays or editing, this bookworm enjoys spending time outdoors hiking and camping.

Natural Leader: If you’ve got a problem, Donor 15512 will solve it. Since an early age, he’s liked to take charge; he was the president of his high school class and the captain of his state championship-winning high school soccer team. Like many of the best leaders, this donor has an impressive work ethic and remains very loyal to those closest to him. He’s also even-keeled and quick with a laugh. He enjoys testing his analytical thinking with strategy-based computer games. An avid hiking enthusiast, he once hiked the treacherous but stunning Tiger Leaping Gorge in China.

More Science Than Fiction: Hardworking, personable, and kind, Donor 15516 has the qualities to become a wonderful doctor. This med student enjoys helping others and worked as a counselor for autistic children. His goal is to become a trusted and affable physician, who both patients and colleagues can approach without hesitation. When he’s not busy studying, he enjoys reading science fiction books and creating clay models of his favorite comic strips. He stays active by running, biking, and swimming.

Artsy Architect: Donor 15517 may have to design a shelf big enough to display all four of his college degrees! Intelligent and talented, he fulfilled his lifelong dream of becoming an architect. Skilled in drawing, contracting, and interior design, this blue-eyed artist sketches constantly and loves photography. Music is another passion of his, as he plays the piano and the drums. He maintains a healthy lifestyle by exercising and monitoring his diet, sleep, and stress levels. Very close with his family, he values the time they spend together. He’s glad to be in our program to provide an opportunity for others to start a family of their own.

Staff Favorite: Charismatic, jovial, and gregarious, Donor 15533 makes a splash when he walks into our office. Intelligent and attractive, this pre-med student, model, actor, soccer MVP, and Latin dance instructor can do just about anything. Determined to live his life to the fullest, he speaks 3 languages and has traveled to nearly 20 countries. Eager to help others, he joined Engineers Without Borders and looks forward to helping people achieve their dream of having a family.

Above The Rim: With dimples and a winning smile, Donor 15550’s face lights up when he talks about his little girl. This proud dad appreciates the tremendous amount of joy his daughter has brought him and finds it very meaningful to participate in our donor program. Although he may seem like a softie, this former college basketball player is fiercely competitive with a self-assured demeanor and Type A personality. As a financial advisor, he has a very strong work ethic and is able to easily adapt to situations and grow.  He enjoys music, drawing, and can fix just about anything.

Athletic Engineer: When Donor 15551 sets his mind to do something, he gives it 110%. Organized and diligent, this chemical engineering PhD student was a college athlete, and now he’s a powerlifter. His high GPA and muscular arms are evidence of his hard work and perseverance. Even in high school, his basketball coach recognized his determination and focus. Despite being serious about his goals, he makes time for hiking, playing golf, or putting on a Santa beard for the family Christmas card photo.

Perfect Score: Driven and hardworking, Donor 15557 started his first business at a young age. This economics major is proud to have graduated from college debt free and his mom is proud of her son’s math skills (he got a perfect SAT math score). In addition to being good at numbers, he was on his high school basketball, football, and swim teams. He also played the saxophone and drums. Energetic and outgoing, working in sales helped him to become more gregarious. Although he has his sights set on advancing his career and traveling the world, he is close with his siblings and makes time for his family.

Proud to Serve: When you see his warm brown eyes, clean-cut hairstyle, and muscular physique, it may seem obvious that Donor 15563 is a military officer in training. (Adult Photos Available) Disciplined and determined, he worked graveyard shifts while going to school full time. Ready for any challenge, he is skilled in machining, fluent in Spanish, and is an avid history buff. He maintains his strength by weight training, practicing jiu-jitsu, and playing sports.  Although he’s strong and tough on the outside, this friendly and caring role model has a tender heart.

Positive Vibes: Smart, sweet, and sporty, Donor 15564 is an optimistic computer science major that is always up to something. On any day of the week, you may catch him speaking French, playing soccer, surfing, or solving logic puzzles. He enjoys classic rock and plays the saxophone, ukulele, and drums. This Fleetwood Mac fan wrote about his favorite song in his Express Yourself. Not afraid to try new things, he joined his college radio station and unexpectedly became a sports announcer.

In high school, this athletic MVP not only played football and basketball, but also played in the jazz band. Focused on looking good and staying healthy, he keeps up his physique by doing Muay Thai, Jiu-Jitsu, yoga, pilates, and kickboxing.

description: Doting Dad: Donor 15581 has small children of his own and is committed to helping others reach their own family goals. Friendly and social, his mantra is to live life with no regrets and to not stress over the small things – which may have helped him become a successful professional. This family man is quite athletic and physically striking; it’s thus little surprise that he was once asked to take a picture with a stranger who’d mistaken him for Derek Jeter!

Healthy, Wealthy, & Wise: Donor 15584 is a successful investor in real estate and the stock market, and credits his success to his analytical and rational approach to problem-solving. He hopes that his professional success will allow him the freedom to spend more time doing what he truly loves, like traveling the world and learning about new cultures. He plans to someday write a book about his success in the stock market. This friendly, even-tempered PhD graduate speaks several languages and really enjoys cooking. A former state roller hockey champion, he also participates in swimming, running, and weight training.

Citizen of the World: Sophisticated, ambitious, and adventurous, Donor 15593 loves to learn and explore. Although this bi-lingual economics major has lived in multiple countries, he maintains a close relationship with his loving and supportive family. Logical and curious, he is a competitive chess player who enjoys Sudoku puzzles, math, and chemistry. His warm and friendly smile is a reflection of his relaxed and fun personality. Glad to help others have children, his Express Yourself is entitled, “A Letter to Offspring”.

Top Chef: Motivated and hardworking, Donor 15601 grew up by the seaside in Turkey and was inspired by his mother to become a professional chef. After finishing his business courses, he pursued his love of culinary arts. You can see a photo of one of his favorite dishes in his Express Yourself and he provides some cooking tips in his Donor Conversation. His two sanctuaries are the kitchen and the sea. When he was young, his father taught him how to dive. He thoroughly enjoys swimming, snorkeling, and fishing. Friendly with a gracious smile, this driven dreamer loves his life.

Captain Compassion: Friendly and big-hearted, Donor 15613 is an active volunteer at his local food bank. Determined and hardworking, he went back to school to pursue his dream of becoming a psychologist to help others. He currently works with disadvantaged people and looks forward to expanding this altruistic role. Athletic and active, he plays soccer, baseball, and was captain of his high school crew team. A fan of the outdoors, he loves hiking and going skiing. He enjoys journaling and has a knack for drawing. His life goal is to open his own psychology practice someday.

Natural Talent: Gifted in math and science, Donor 15620 followed in his parents’ footsteps by becoming a software engineer, even though they advised it would be a difficult career. Intelligent and determined, he commits himself 100% to any activity or relationship he pursues. After his sister introduced him to yoga, he continued to take classes, and now he’s a certified instructor. He has a knack for excelling at diverse hobbies, ranging from playing guitar to rock climbing to painting. Logical, yet empathetic, this dog-lover has a positive attitude, bright smile, and a deep focus on family.

Heart & Soul: Intelligent, outgoing, and attractive, Donor 15634 has dedicated his career to helping others. Proud of earning 3 degrees, he plans to continue his education and earn a Doctor of Psychology. He provides counseling to women and children in underserved communities, volunteers his time mentoring homeless kids, and even received a community leadership award. Organized, conscientious, and self-disciplined, this altruistic overachiever also has a playful side. He enjoys tearing up the dance floor and playing pranks on April Fool’s Day. Fit and strong, he won medals in track and field, lifts weights, and does cardio. (Adult Photos Available)

Worldly Geophysicist: As a child, Donor 15645 loved to take apart and fix old electronics to see how they worked. This research physicist and former forest firefighter is intellectually curious and has a wide range of interests. Repairing old bicycles, learning new languages, and playing chess are just a few of his hobbies. Gifted in math, fond of writing, and an avid reader, he may often have his nose in a book, but he enjoys getting out to ski, snowboard, and play golf.

The Write Stuff: Creative with a business mind, Donor 15647 earned his MBA and enjoys working on movies. Passionate about writing stories, his goal is to share one of his stories on the big screen for all to see. In addition to film, he appreciates all types of cultural activities like concerts, plays, and art exhibits. His love of music started as a youngster when he played the piano and saxophone. Also fond of traveling, he snowboards, scuba dives, and would love to learn how to fly a plane.

Brain and Lung Power: A 4.0 student through high school, college, and graduate school, 15650 is one smart cookie. He’s a composer, musician, writer, and trivia-enthusiast who loves all the absurdity and uniqueness the world has to offer. At 6’2”, he is right at home on any basketball court, but also loves a heated ping-pong match, or ripping down the slopes on his snowboard. Although many people can play the saxophone, this Doctor of Musical Arts has the PhD to prove he can blow with the best of them.

Creative Soul: Donor 15651 loves contributing to the well-being of humanity through the arts. A musician and an artist, he enjoys performing his electronic music and showing his art in galleries. Sincere with a warm heart, he appreciates the small things in life and practices meditation. When he’s not creating masterpieces, he enjoys kayaking, hiking, and snowboarding. A combination of silly and serious, he is fascinated by the deep questions of life, he’s devoted to his wife and family, and he likes to sport a fanny pack.

“Eight Days a Week”: An aficionado of music, art, and sports, Donor 15664 is a talented overachiever who hones his craft daily.  This Beatles fan started playing the piano when he was just five years old and he sings every day. He also plays percussion and was music director of a collegiate a cappella group. Having grown up in an artistic family, it’s no surprise that he’s skilled at drawing and painting. He combines poetry, songwriting, and lyrics to create his art. Muscular and active, he works out six days a week, loves playing and coaching baseball, and also participates in triathlons. Sensitive and caring, he enjoys giving back to his community. (Adult Photos Available)

description: Kind & Clever: Fluent in Hindi and English, Donor 15665 scored excellent distinction on his exams and received an award in the Mathematics Olympiad contest. Courageous and eager to try new things, he embraced the opportunity when he unexpectedly got transferred to the U.S. for work. This software engineer earned multiple engineering degrees and is proud of his situation analyzing capabilities. He’s also proud of the volunteer work that he does with children. He believes that children deserve to be happy and devotes his free time to teaching them ping pong and distributing toys to kids in need. Fond of cricket, tennis, and soccer, he won sports awards in school. He stays in shape now by going to the gym a few times a week.

Worldly Wordsmith: Proud to have served our country, Donor 15678’s military service allowed him to immerse himself in a different culture overseas. Deeply curious and open to new experiences, he is passionate about traveling. This international affairs graduate speaks Arabic fluently and can also converse in Polish and Spanish. When he isn’t busy at work writing, he enjoys playing chess, sailing, and dancing salsa & bachata. Thoughtful and reflective, check out the insightful life lessons that he shares with future offspring in his Donor Essay.

Trilingual Techie: Donor 15680 views life as a gift. He comes from a large family and appreciates the close connections that he has with his relatives and lifelong friends. This MBA grad is grateful to his parents for everything they did for him and is devoted to caring for them. He makes the most out of each day by learning new things and exploring. Fluent in Hindi and Gujarati, he loves listening to songs in those languages. This software engineering manager enjoys building robots and reading, but also likes to stay active playing sports like cricket, golf, soccer, tennis, and doing yoga.

Happy-Go-Lucky: Open-minded and friendly, Donor 15687 is a kinesiology student with a passion for exercise, cooking, and art. Being active makes him happy and he maintains his athletic physique by playing basketball, baseball, football, and swimming. He is thankful that his father taught him how to skateboard when he was child, as it has brought him many years of enjoyment. Creative and artsy, he’s skilled at drawing and painting. He’s also a whiz in the kitchen and loves making new recipes with his wife. This proud husband is grateful for his blissful marriage and doesn’t take anything for granted.

Model of Success: Tall and muscular with bright blue eyes and a dazzling smile, Donor 15690 maintains a healthy organic diet and is always on the go. Sports and fitness come easily to this versatile athlete who plays football, swims, and snowboards. Model, actor, personal trainer, and real estate agent, he’s done it all. But he’s most proud of starting a business when he was a 20-year-old college student and watching it still thrive. In addition to being ambitious, intelligent, and very disciplined, he also enjoys helping others. His volunteer work includes building houses with Habitat for Humanity.

description: Family Matters: Positive and easygoing, it doesn’t take much to make Donor 15696 content. Just give him some PB&J sandwiches and time with his dogs and siblings, and he’s happy. One of six children, he appreciates having a big family and protects his little brothers and sisters. He enjoys going to concerts and watching movies with them. This hopeless romantic likes to read romance novels, which all started when his librarian gave him a book recommendation. Always laughing, he likes to express himself by singing and dancing (badly). Fond of outdoor activities, he enjoys going to the beach, hiking, and playing baseball.

Friendly Front-Runner: Outgoing, empathetic, and optimistic, Donor 15705 is truly a people person who wants to create positive change. This cheerful go-getter fits his Keirsey assessment of a “Champion”. These kindhearted and enthusiastic idealists suited to become inspirational leaders are apparently very rare, representing only 2-3% of the population. With a master’s degree in public policy, he plans to pursue a career in politics and tackle social issues. Captain of his high school baseball team, president of his class, and founder of a non-profit, he has the drive and leadership ability to accomplish his goals. He also has a sense of balance, enjoying reflective hobbies like surfing, mediation, and yoga.

Makes Science Look Cool: One look at his Adult Photos and you can tell Donor 15708 isn’t your average math and science student. Yes, he enjoys tinkering with electronics. Yes, he can build computers. And yes, he was in the National Honors Society, but this friendly and inquisitive scholar has style! A member of the hip-hop club, he enjoys dancing, drawing, and writing music. He even earned a certificate in film studies. Tri-lingual, he speaks English, Nepali, and Japanese. He stays active playing tennis, soccer, and rowing crew. Most importantly, he strives to put 100% into everything that he does.

The Quiet Creative: Soft-spoken and focused on learning new things, Donor 15713 is incredibly creative. This talented musician plays several instruments and graduated in the top of his class. In addition to being skilled in music composition and audio engineering, he also knows his way around a kitchen. This foodie is a fantastic cook who enjoys everything from Lebanese cuisine to sushi to craft burgers. His hobbies include photography, reading, and amateur rally driving. He has a knack for auto detailing and car maintenance.

Fit & Focused Filmmaker: Donor 15721 isn’t afraid to push his limits. Lean and muscular, this triathlete loves working out at the gym. Methodical by nature and physically fit, he trained with the ROTC. This analytical thinker has a good head on his shoulders and is passionate about his film work. Charismatic and social, he’s a great conversationalist. Always up for an adventure, he’s interested in learning about different cultures and trying new things.

Animated Actor: First in his family to attend and graduate college, Donor 15725 is proud to have set a trend for his younger brothers. Although he majored in graphic design and loves screen printing, his passion for acting drew him to the camera. Always ready for a good laugh, he’s especially fond of dad jokes and cat videos. He enjoys exercising and lifting weights to stay in shape.

Aspiring Astronaut: Bold, confident, and intelligent, Donor 15727 has been fascinated with aviation and space since he was 8 years old. At age 13, he went skydiving for the first time and jumped out of a Russian bi-plane 1,000 meters above the ground. He’s done 169 jumps, acquired his parachute license, and earned a commercial pilot’s license. His next goal is working for NASA. In addition to his passion for flying, he enjoys helping others. Active in the U.S. military, he participated in search and rescue missions during natural disasters. Physically fit with big green eyes and a can-do attitude, this motivated aviator is going places. (Adult Photos Available)

Blue-Eyed Optimist: Ambitious, intelligent, and witty, Donor 15737 excels at math and science. Empathetic and altruistic, this former boy scout learned to get over his fear of needles when he found out that the Red Cross greatly needed donors with his blood type. Quick with a clever quip, this articulate computer scientist is also a film buff who loves stand-up comedy. He shares a list of his favorite movies and TV shows in his Express Yourself. Social with a positive outlook on life, he treasures the time he spends with his friends. He also enjoys swimming, snowboarding, and playing strategy board games.

A-List Athlete: Smart, driven, and hardworking, Donor 15749 sets high goals for himself. This elite level hockey player also earned MVP for his high school football team, all while maintaining his A average. He was on the Dean’s List every semester in college and in law school, he earned the highest grade in one of his classes. Inspired by Ari from the show Entourage, his strong passion for sports and stellar academic background helped him achieve his dream job as a sports agent. Fit and active, he also enjoys adventurous activities like skydiving and heli skiing.

Triple Threat: Outgoing, creative, and filled with enthusiasm, Donor 15757 was already a writer, musician, and dancer at age 8. From tap dancing, to hip hop, to screenwriting, his passion for the arts runs deep. Not just an artist, this multi-talented scholar-athlete earned varsity letters for 3 sports in high school and graduated summa cum laude from college. Fond of nature, he enjoys hiking and mountain biking. Slender with a full head of curly strawberry blond hair, hazel eyes, and dimples, this aspiring filmmaker can’t wait to share his stories with an audience.

Shooting Star: Donor 15759 is confident, determined, and athletic. This talented college basketball player and honor student earned a degree in Business Administration. Passionate about writing, he hopes to see one of his screenplays at the box office someday. He also enjoys writing comedic skits and is inspired by Larry David. In addition to working out and playing virtually every sport, he also plays the piano and bass guitar. This analytical thinker likes to play board games and even created his own game. Be sure to check out his Adult Photos!

Keyboard Master: When not sitting at one keyboard or another, this software engineer and amateur composer can often be found on the tennis or basketball court. A self-motivated and disciplined student, he credits his strong relationship with his mother as an important part of his academic success. He is kind to all creatures and believes we need to protect Mother Earth. Although video games are a major hobby, he also sees the damage they can cause if not played in moderation.

Work Hard, Play Hard: Driven and intelligent, when Donor 15857 was just 10 years old, he started his first business so he could buy his mom a necklace. (He’s already been to 41 states!)

Slender and toned, he works out regularly by playing tennis, doing Muay Thai, and lifting weights. He started playing piano at a young age and likes to play classical music. You can get a sense of his easygoing personality from listening to his Donor Conversation.
